Objectives: -
The factors and objectives that shape up the bank’s policies towards credit risk
management are:
• To make available sufficient liquidity to meet loan ailments, interest, operational
and other costs and losses.
• To maximize profits
• To support broad national policy objectives of liquidity, interest rate stability,
financial stability and above all, allocation of scarce financial resources efficiently to
foster economic growth.
The management of credit risk should receive the top management’s attention and the
process should encompass
a. Measurement of risk through credit rating/scoring
b. Quantifying the risk through estimating expected loan losses
c. Risk pricing on a scientific basis 
d. Controlling the risk through effective Loan Review Mechanism and portfolio
management. 
